1.	What is a code repository (often also called version control system) used for?
A Code repository is a place to store all source code, related documents, local or online repositories and source code version control.
2.	Why is it advantageous to use a code repository?
It’s advantageous to use a code repository because its keep your code safe and store files you want to protect them
3.	Describe the different “layers” of Software that exist on a typical computer and explain why there are different layers of software.
A. Application software, which used by the computer system to perform a special functions or provide entertainment functions beyond the basic operation of the computer itself.
B. System software, which is designed to directly operate the computer hardware, to provide basic functionality needed by users and other software, and to provide a platform for running application software and include the operating systems, device drivers and the utilities.
C. Malicious software, which are computer programs developed to harm and disrupt computers.
There are different layers of software because the range of tasks that can be performed with a modern computer is so large.
4.	Describe what an algorithm is and explain why it is a useful “tool” to translate from a human level problem (we can think of) to a computer program.
In computer science, an algorithm is a self-contained step-by-step set of operations to be performed. Also is a procedure or formula for solving a problem. It’s a useful tool because CPU only understands machine language instructions Programs that are written in a high-level language must be translated into machine language Depending on the language that a program has been written in, the programmer will use either a compiler or an interpreter to make the translation.
