6.	Is Idle (the Python language shell) an Interpreter or an Compiler or both? Explain your answer.
The Python language uses an interpreter, which is a program that both translates and executes the instructions in a high-level language program Interpreters combine translation and execution, they typically do not create separate machine language programs.

